p: Comparing compound 181 (IC 50: D6 = 39 ng/mL − W2 = 20 ng/mL) with compound 181a (IC 50: D6 = >10000 ng/mL − W2 = 840 ng/mL), compound 181b (IC 50: D6 = 2580 ng/mL − W2 = 980 ng/mL), and compound 181c (IC 50: D6 = 4210 ng/mL − W2 = 2440 ng/mL) a decrease in activity was noted when unsaturation was reduced ( 181a), epoxidation to the 1,2-β-epoxy derivative ( 181b), or unsaturation and ketone reductions to 1,2 dihydro-β-gedunol ( 181c). In all these cases, activity against both clones was reduced, mainly D6.
